cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper is about image generation using a novel method that combines the strengths of existing methods while overcoming their drawbacks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses alternative methods for image generation, which suggests that it could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well. The use of nearest-neighbor based implicit maximum likelihood estimation (IMLE) and latent embedding learning methods (e.g. GLO) also suggests that it could be classified under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and graphics (cs.GR) categories.
